On some of my PRs (eg: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/69119) I see pending CI checks:
```Instabase - CI: Expected â€” Waiting for status to be reported```
Might this be related to the incident? How can I retrigger them? :slightly_smiling_face:
I force pushed to my branch with an empty commit to retrigger them
Ah yea, if you just hit `Rebuild` on the CI job in Jenkins it'll re-build that CI test run and should pass
The PRs aren't linking to the jenkins jobs, but I guess it would also work to go to jenkins and try to find the jobs for the PR!
Ooh gotcha! Yea in that case a `git rebase master && git push origin -f` like you said ~Lydia~ Jessica (got my conversations mixed up! sorry!), would work well :slightly_smiling_face:
